 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umediteman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mediteman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/27/02 2:53:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Raid</span><hr size=1> Tarin:<br>
<br>
Since you signed up for the Naggy Raid that I will be leading this Sunday, I assumed that you would be willing to follow me in the Naggy portion of the raid.<br>
<br>
Given your comments and concerns, I reiterate that I will be leading the open Naggy raid (as I have done in the past and will continue to do in the future unless someone else requests the opportunity to lead them).  <br>
<br>
The Vox portion of this raid is premised upon and presupposes that Fumin will be unsuccessful in taking down Vox.  From what I understand, Fumin's &quot;failures&quot; have not been due to lack of skill; rather, he has simply been trying to take down Vox with as few as 16 players.  If Fumin is able to gather sufficient forces, I am sure that Vox will go down as planned.<br>
<br>
While I understand that you believe you have your &quot;own style&quot; of running hunts, your extensive use of Findra's instructions in your Naggy Raid post last week suggests otherwise.  <br>
<br>
In addition, I attended your Naggy raid last week and have an understanding of how you conduct your hunts.  The only differences I saw in the way we conduct Naggy Raids were the following:<br>
<br>
1.  Instead of sending everyone into Sol B at the same time, I generally follow Findra's advice and send one group in to clear a path to the stone spider room.  The other groups then follow and simply walk into the stone spider room.  This avoids the problem of having a bunch of people stuck in the halls if they are all sent in at the same time.<br>
<br>
2.  Rather than bringing people into the throne room after killing the two guards at the gate, I usually follow Findra's advice and pull all the giants in the throne room area before moving people up.  This obviates the need to fight five giants in the throne room area.<br>
<br>
3.  If someone decides to gate (despite specific instructions not to gate), I generally do not go back to retrieve that person unless (a) the group is notified beforehand, and (b) it can be done without jeopardizing the safety of the group.<br>
<br>
4.  Rather than moving people across the lava bridge to fight the roamer in the antechamber area, I usually follow Findra's advice and have someone bow pull the roamer and kill him up in the throne room area.<br>
<br>
5.  Rather than having everyone stand on the bridge over the lava while waiting for the giants to be pulled in the antechamber area, I usually follow Findra's advice and allow them to stand in the back part of L shaped antechamber area.<br>
<br>
6.  I generally name a 52 warrior as a main assist (if available) because they have an evasive discipline that means they take less damage and require less healing (and rezzing).  If there are several 52 warriors, I compare ac, hps, and weapons in determining the main assist.<br>
<br>
7.  I usually name the second highest level warrior as a secondary assist, if available.<br>
<br>
8.  I usually bring a few stacks of peridots with me and hand them out to all the clerics.  If people are inclined to make donations to me to help cover this cost, I accept them.  Otherwise, I generally keep all throwing boulders and perhaps a small ring to help defray the costs of the peridots.<br>
<br>
If the foregoing differences are not too much of an imposition on the way you conduct hunts, perhaps you would be willing to participate and assist in the success of the Naggy portion of the Double Dragon Sunday as I participated in and contributed to the success of your Naggy Raid last week.  Again, all of this assumes that Fumin will be unsuccessful on Saturday.<br>
<br>
As a renowned intellectual once remarked, if I have come far it is because I have stood on the shoulders of giants.  Relying on the advice and experience and teaching of others does not diminish our accomplishments.  However, seeking to take credit without acknowledging these contributions comes off as vain and egotistical.<br>
<br>
If Fumin does not succeed and it is possible to take down two dragons in one day, let's check our egos and our vanity at the door, work together as a team, and make this proposed event a success for all concerned.  Those who have pledged to follow us into battle deserve no less.<br>
<br>
Medite Marconus <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umediteman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mediteman</A> at: 9/27/02 3:56:17 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucryo1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cryo1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/27/02 3:19:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=113.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> aaeb</span><hr size=1> <br>
